node.text:
More than the launch of unparalleled works of jewelry craft, @Bulgari's Magnifica High Jewelry collection is a celebration of rebirth. Honored through magnificent muses, music, and Milan, take a look at Bvlgari's latest high jewelry collection.
 
Models: @vittoria, @lilyaldridge @heconghc, @solangesmith and @blesnyaminher
Special Guests: @andreabocelliofficial @beatricevenezi
Project by @oma.eu
Director @tommaso.ottomano
DOP@ mrcodepa
Stylist @sagliogeraldine
Music @guazzonemarco 
Production @studio.april
#Bvlgari #BvlgariJewelry #BvlgariHighJewelry #BvlgariMagnifica #Milan

node.text: After making her #NYFW modeling debut at @ProenzaSchouler, @EllaEmhoff landed a knitwear collaboration with Batsheva Hay (@batshevadress). The 21-year-old student, model, and designer met up with Hay amid NYFW—and #GoodMorningVogue was there to capture their conversations about materials, fit, and texture, plus Ella's rise to fame in the wake of the inauguration of President Joe Biden and Emhoff’s step-mother, Kamala Harris, in January.

node.text: This month, Vogue joined forces with an army of photographers and models all around the globe—stable Zoom connections required, please!—and sent the best and brightest of the new collections via courier services everywhere from Beijing to Brazil, Lagos to Los Angeles. Our concept? Simple, glorious movement: After a year of stasis, immobility and lockdowns, we wanted to see spring fashion breaking free. These are the looks we love, shot by the photographers we adore, on the run and out for a walk, a swim, a dance. Tap the link in our bio to see more.

node.text:
Today, @KamalaHarris became the first woman of color ever sworn in as vice president of the United States.

To celebrate this moment, twelve young women discussing what it means to them to see a Black woman of Indian descent elected to the second-highest office in the land. “Every little girl sees that this is a country of possibility,” @KamalaHarris states in one address, and that sentiment is widely echoed. “She reminds me every day that I am capable and worthy of my wildest dreams,” says one participant.

Director @rombokob
Producer @aliwebb_producer
Casting Director: Rebecca Dealy
Archival Research: Manon Blackman
Editor @ann_lupo
GFX @horatiobaltz
Color @carlosfloresfilms
Mix @cstropko
Post Production @forager.tv

node.title: 12 Girls on What Kamala Harris Becoming Vice President Means to Them

node.text: Throughout the political tumult of 2020, @janayathefuture was one of the most prominent voices to become a source of healing and hope. Reflecting on this week’s events, Khan points out the lack of police presence at the Capitol, a fact that exposes, in their own words, “a clear double standard for how Black protestors have been treated over the past several years. What we know to be true is that there is a way that white rage is celebrated in this country and Black grief is criminalized.” To hear more, make sure to check out Khan’s Sunday Sermons, returning tomorrow 1/10  at 12PM PST on their account.

node.title: @janayathefuture on Moving Forward from the Capitol Riots

node.text:
Upon seeing her final look for the 2021 #MetGala, @CaraDelevingne got emotional. “I nearly burst into tears; I felt so grateful,” she says. “It’s my most simple Met piece, but it says it all for itself.” 

At the link in our bio, the star shares a glimpse into her getting-ready process and the feminist message behind her @Dior look. 
Director: @annamalize
DP: @aliceplati
Editor: @__katiewolford__
AC: @luisr.omero 
Audio: @rachelsuff
Location: @themarkhotelny

node.text:
For her first appearance at the #Metgala, Representative @AOC had to make a political statement. It was only right. And since she was at fashion’s glitziest night, surrounded by some of the most powerful and famous people in the world, what better medium to get her message out about taxing the rich than, well, to have it written in red on her dress? The Democratic socialist congresswoman wore a white gown by @BrotherVellies, splashed with the political slogan across the back.

“We can never get too comfortable in our seats at the table once they’ve been given,” @AuroraJames, founder and creative director of Brother Vellies and the founder of the @15PercentPledge says. “We must always continue to push ourselves, push our colleagues, push the culture, and push the country forward. Fashion is changing; America is changing. And as far as this theme goes, I think Alexandria and I are a great embodiment of the language fashion needs to consider adding to the general lexicon as we work towards a more sustainable, inclusive, and empowered future.”

Tap the link in our bio for an inside look at the duo's #MetGala prep.

K-Pop superstar Rosé (@roses_are_rosie) made her #MetGala debut this year. As one-fourth of the record-breaking girl group Blackpink and a solo artist whose album, R, dropped earlier this year, Rosé is pop royalty.

Still, even she was nervous while preparing for her first trip to the gala, which she shares in a new Vogue video. “My expectation is for me to totally blackout and get nervous and freeze,” she shared. “[Still] I hope that everything is the opposite of that.”

Tap the link in our bio for a look at how the popstar got ready in @ysl by @anthonyvaccarello for her very first Met gala.

node.text:
No one is more excited for the new #Dune film than @Grimes. For the 2021 #MetGala, Grimes and her stylist, @TurnerTurner, say their first conversation about what look they wanted to create ultimately brought the pair to Frank Herbert’s American novel, Dune, adapted into both David Lynch’s 1984 film and next month’s iteration.

“We were working with the Dune movie people,” Grimes explains, noting that they’d planned to sort of “hire me as a professional fan, or like, an influencer or something,” she laughs. No official contracts happened in time, so the unofficial look is “Dune-esque.”

Tap the link in our bio for an inside look at Grimes's #Metgala night.

Director: @changeme2012
DP: @phileysanneh
Editor: @savannafair
AC: @dom_a_rama
Audio: @ziongatefilms

node.text:
For the 2021 #MetGala, “In America: A Lexicon of Fashion,” co-chair @BillieEilish turned to one of the biggest names in U.S. fashion to craft her ode to a woman that defined American culture.

Eilish teamed up with @OscardeLaRenta to create a look paying homage to Marilyn Monroe. Several months and toile fittings later, Eilish had her finished red-carpet look: a sustainable ombré gown that’s featherlight despite being dramatically voluminous. “I find it shocking that wearing fur isn’t completely outlawed at this point in 2021,” Eilish said. “I am so beyond thrilled that Fernando and Laura and the rest of the Oscar de la Renta team heard me on this issue and have made a change that not only makes an impact for the greater good for animals but also for our planet and environment too. I’m honored to have been a catalyst and to have been heard on this matter. I urge all designers to do the same.”

Tap the link in our bio to get ready with Eilish and the Oscar de la Renta team for the 2021 #MetGala.

Director: @maxbartick
DP: @frankapollonio, @rachelbatashvili
Editor: @bigbabyreuter
AC: @zanderthewizard
Audio: @seanpaulsen
Location: @themarkhotelny

node.text:
“How do I feel in the dress? It’s definitely heavy, but I feel beautiful, strong, and empowered,” @SimoneBiles said at the final fitting for her #MetGala dress. Designed by Beckett Fogg and Piotrek Panszczyk of @Area, the three-in-one outfit consists of a hand-embellished skirt covered in Swarovski crystals and weighing 88 pounds; a minidress underneath; and a glittering black catsuit decorated to look like a starry night sky (though each of the stars is really @Athleta’s logo, the chi).

At the link in our bio, take a look at the creative process involved with Biles's look at the 2021 #MetGala. Photographed by @thedenisestephanie

node.text:
@OliviaRodrigo made her #MetGala debut this year, adding to a huge year for the 18-year-old singer-songwriter. For fashion's biggest night out, Rodrigo went for something different: a high glamour, black lace catsuit by @YSL by @anthonyvaccarello with a feathered neckline, marking a new and edgier chapter in her fashion journey. 

At the link in our bio, go behind the scenes with Olivia Rodrigo as she prepares for her first-ever Met gala red carpet. 
Director: @thisismayan
DP: @alexa_mini
Editor: @dpoler
AC: @thommarch
Audio: @recordconnect
Location: @fasanofifthavenue
